The following are the resources for NOISE corpus to refine our data if we hear noise instead of speech


https://www.noisli.com/
this is for random or custom noise

http://www.orangefreesounds.com/background-noise-sound-pack/
a free background noise pacv 

https://freesound.org/browse/tags/background-sound/
https://freesound.org/browse/tags/noise/
https://freesound.org/search/?q=india
this is a big database of free background sound but we need to find the sound required for the project

http://soundbible.com/954-Background-Noise.html
this is also a free source but selection to be done manually

http://www.fon.hum.uva.nl/IFA-SpokenLanguageCorpora/IFAcorpus/
these people seem to have a speech and nonspeech corpus availble with transcripts but these fuckers just dont want to give them to the public
